criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age 18 years or older;

          -  laboratory-confirmed COVID-19 patients;

          -  radiographic evidence of pulmonary inflammation;

          -  clear consciousness and ability to communicate verbally;

          -  patients who have undergone prone position ventilation at least once during
             hospitalization;

        Exclusion Criteria:

        • Patients who were mechanically ventilated with oral intubation immediately after
        admission or 2 h after admission.
